news.title: Navi Mumbai’s civic body becomes first in country to provide property identity cards to citizens
news.para: Navi Mumbai has become the first municipal corporation in India to launch 'Property Identity Cards' for its property holders. Commissioner Kailas Shinde initiated the program, benefiting over 3.5 lakh owners by providing easy access to property details and tax information. The card streamlines property transactions and facilitates online payments, enhancing transparency and efficiency within the property tax department.

news.title: A bellwether signal? SBI hikes home loan rates by 25 basis points
news.para: State Bank of India and Union Bank of India have increased home loan rates, signaling a potential shift towards higher interest rates in the market, particularly affecting borrowers with lower credit scores. This move comes amid concerns over low-profit margins and increased competition, with private lenders expressing reservations about aggressive pricing strategies employed by public sector banks.

news.title: Banks widen home loan spreads to save margins
news.para: To safeguard their profitability, SBI and Union Bank of India are increasing home loan spreads despite falling policy rates. This reverses the trend of passing rate cuts to new borrowers, as banks grapple with sticky deposit costs. Public sector lenders, previously focused on market share, are now prioritizing sustainable returns, signaling a potential shift in the home loan market.

news.title: Delhi: More delay in Signature View Apartments' construction work
news.para: Residents of Delhi's Signature View Apartments, facing imminent demolition, have requested more time to vacate, citing difficulties in finding alternative housing. The RWA has asked for an extension until October 1st, highlighting a previously agreed-upon deadline. While DDA has started compensatory rent for some, a manpower shortage is hindering further agreements.

news.title: PM inaugurates two major National Highway projects worth ₹11,000 crore
news.para: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated the Delhi section of the Dwarka Expressway and the Urban Extension Road-II (UER-II) in Delhi, developed at a cost of Rs. 5,360 crore and Rs 5,580 crores respectively. These projects aim to decongest Delhi, improve connectivity, reduce travel time, and ease traffic on key routes, enhancing mobility and industrial connectivity in the NCR region.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body set to transfer 76 supervisors
news.para: The Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) is transferring 76 supervisors due to complaints of collusion with contractors, facilitating illegal construction. Residents allege supervisors demand money to ignore unauthorized floors. The reshuffle aims to curb the rise of illegal colonies, fueled by supervisors forming alliances with local realtors over several years.

news.title: Tamil Nadu to roll out ‘presenceless’ system in property registration
news.para: Tamil Nadu's registration department is preparing to introduce a presenceless registration system for property transactions, starting with an optional phase for first-sale registrations of apartments and plots. This initiative aims to reduce congestion at sub-registrar offices and streamline the process by allowing online registration and verification.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh real estate sector shows signs of recovery
news.para: Andhra Pradesh's real estate sector is showing signs of recovery after a five-year lull, with land transactions increasing across the state. A 46% revenue growth in stamps and registrations during the first quarter indicates renewed investor interest, particularly in Amaravati, driving growth in Krishna, Guntur, and Palnadu districts.

news.title: DDA's land licensing model bags ₹10,000 crore deal
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has awarded its first Special License Property (SLP) project to Fleur Hotels, a Lemon Tree Hotels subsidiary, projecting a revenue of Rs 10,000 crore over 55 years. Fleur Hotels secured the 2-acre Nehru Place land parcel, earmarked for a five-star hotel, with an annual license fee of Rs 27.19 crore.

news.title: Turning Noida into metropolitan council will need change in law
news.para: The Supreme Court has asked the Uttar Pradesh government to consider replacing the Noida Authority. The replacement would be with a metropolitan council for better governance. This direction follows a report highlighting issues like centralized decision-making and lack of transparency. The court has ordered immediate actions. These include appointing a vigilance officer and forming a citizen advisory board.

news.title: Mahindra looks to acquire 350-acre land parcel in Igatpuri
news.para: Mahindra & Mahindra has expressed interest in acquiring 350 acres in Igatpuri, Maharashtra, to potentially establish a supplier park or expand facilities for its Nashik and Igatpuri plants, according to Executive Director Rajesh Jejurikar. CEO Nalinikanth Gollagunta also revealed plans to increase production capacity at the Chakan plant by 2.

news.title: Telangana CM to launch Indiramma housing ceremonies by August-end
news.para: Telangana's Chief Minister A Revanth Reddy and Housing Minister Ponguleti Srinivas Reddy are set to launch 'gruhapravesam' ceremonies for newly-built Indiramma houses before the panchayat elections. The Congress government has allocated ₹22,500 crore for Indiramma housing in each constituency, aiming to fulfill the housing dreams of the poor, including Chenchu tribals. The first phase targets completing 4.

news.title: Gurugram: 400 evacuated residents wait as district administration calls for audit by experts
news.para: Following the collapse of a retaining wall at a construction site in Sector 69, Gurugram, hundreds of Neelkanth Enclave residents face prolonged displacement. PWD's initial inspection deemed the damaged buildings unsafe, prompting a comprehensive structural audit by IIT-Delhi or CBRI experts.

news.title: Panvel civic body recovers ₹167 crore property tax in amnesty period
news.para: Panvel City Municipal Corporation recovered ₹167 crore in property tax from over 60,000 property holders. An amnesty scheme provided significant fine exemptions, benefiting thousands. However, a large protest, involving multiple political parties, erupted over the levied property tax, which they claim is excessive and unjustified for a 'D' class municipal corporation.

news.title: DDA to hold phase II of property registration camps in unauthorised colonies on Aug 17
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is set to conduct the second phase of single-window camps on August 17 to facilitate property registration in unauthorized colonies under the PM-UDAY scheme. These camps, organized at ten locations, aim to streamline the process by providing on-the-spot assistance with documentation, registration, and issue resolution.

news.title: MahaRERA to issue warrants to recover ₹90 crore in Palais Royale dispute
news.para: MahaRERA has issued orders for warrants against Honest Shelters. This is to recover about Rs 90 crore in interest. The interest is for delayed possession in the Palais Royale project. IIFL Finance had filed a complaint. The complaint was about non-compliance with a previous order. The order directed Honest Shelters to hand over possession of flats.

news.title: After decade-long ordeal, Bengaluru flat buyers without sale deed win interest payout
news.para: The Karnataka Real Estate Appellate Tribunal (KREAT) has ruled in favor of homebuyers, directing a builder to pay interest on a Rs 34.4 lakh refund. This decision overturns an earlier order by Rera that denied interest despite a nine-year delay in delivering a promised flat.

news.title: Mumbai targets five lakh SRA homes in five years, double its 29-year output
news.para: Mumbai's Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) aims to construct over five lakh homes for slum dwellers in the next five years, more than doubling its 29-year output. Recent reforms, including rule changes, drone surveys, and biometric data collection, have accelerated project delivery.

news.title: After year-long deadlock, Telangana moves to hike property registration values in core urban region
news.para: The Telangana government is set to revise market values for property registration in the core urban region, potentially increasing revenue by ₹2,000-₹2,500 crore annually. Proposed hikes of 30%-50% aim to align official rates with prevailing market prices, especially in high-growth areas. Committees are formed to assess rates, and public feedback will be considered before final implementation.

news.title: Maharashtra CM asks builders why housing prices are rising in Mumbai despite concessions
news.para: Chief Minister Fadnavis expressed concern over rising Mumbai flat prices despite government concessions like reduced premiums. He urged builders to invest in developing Third and Fourth Mumbai, focusing on edutech and innovation hubs. Fadnavis also emphasized the need for faster slum redevelopment using new technologies to achieve a slum-free Mumbai.
